## Section 1: Ranked Shortlist (Top 5)

### #1 — Sudao G.R.E.E.N. Minds *(13/15)*
**Location:** Salcedo, Eastern Samar (provincial; digitally active)
**One-liner:** Pioneer youth-led local climate-action group in a typhoon-frontline coastal town, founded 2019, running cleanups, tree planting, mangrove planting, and disaster risk education with ~50 members.
**Score breakdown:** C1=3 · C2=3 · C3=3 · C4=2 · C5=2
**Why most relevant to SkillSeed:** This is the *archetype* user — a small, hyperlocal, disaster-frontline youth org doing exactly the steady-state + alert-state work SkillSeed is built for. They are formally partnered with ICSC and have a documented public profile (VERA Files, Climate Tracker Asia, ICSC features) but documentation appears to live entirely on Facebook posts and partner-org features — no visible structured verification system of their own. The founder Nezika Berongoy is publicly named, accessible, and the org has institutional credibility through ICSC.
**Best contact channel:** Facebook Messenger to https://www.facebook.com/SudaoGREENMinds.ES/ ; secondary route via ICSC partner contact at https://icsc.ngo
**Recommended outreach approach:** Facebook Messenger first — small provincial youth orgs are most responsive on Messenger; do not cold-email. Lead with the Salcedo climate emergency declaration and the People's Survival Fund advocacy work. Offer a 20-minute Zoom call given the geographic distance from Metro Manila.

