## Section 3: Individual Organization Profiles (Top 5)

### Sudao G.R.E.E.N. Minds

- **Full name:** Sudao Generation Ready for Environmental Education and Action Minds
- **Location:** Salcedo, Eastern Samar (Region VIII / Eastern Visayas)
- **Founded:** 2019
- **Membership:** ~50 members
- **Founder / lead figure:** Nezika Berongoy
- **Facebook:** https://www.facebook.com/SudaoGREENMinds.ES/
- **Primary activities:** Cleanups, tree planting, climate advocacy, mangrove planting, disaster risk education, advocacy for People's Survival Fund and Loss and Damage Fund access for their municipality.
- **Documentation today:** Public profile lives across (a) their own Facebook page, (b) features by partner orgs (ICSC, VERA Files, Climate Tracker Asia). No structured impact reporting system was visible in this search. Most of the organization's documented impact appears in *external* coverage rather than in their own structured records — i.e., others are writing their story for them, which is precisely the verification/documentation gap SkillSeed addresses.
- **DRR connection:** Explicit. Mangrove planting is direct coastal-defense work; "participating in disaster risk education" is in the activity list per ICSC; Salcedo is a frontline typhoon-affected town.
- **Institutional partners:** Institute for Climate and Sustainable Cities (ICSC). Featured in VERA Files and Climate Tracker Asia. Engaged on People's Survival Fund and Loss and Damage Fund processes.
- **Public-post evidence of documentation gap:** ICSC's feature page (https://icsc.ngo/salcedo-youth-advocates-for-local-climate-action/) is itself the documentation infrastructure — i.e., their public proof-of-work depends on a partner NGO writing it up. There is no surfaced equivalent of "Sudao GREEN Minds 2024 Impact Report" or structured mission log. This is the visible gap.
- **Suggested interview question:** "Pag may ginagawa kayong tree planting o mangrove planting sa Salcedo — paano niyo dino-document yung impact niya? Sino yung umuupo at nag-a-aggregate ng records? At kapag may funder o partner na nag-a-ask ng proof, ano yung pinapakita niyo?"

