### YACAP (Youth Advocates for Climate Action Philippines)

- **Full name:** Youth Advocates for Climate Action Philippines, formally registered as Youth Alliance on Climate Justice Inc.
- **Founded:** 2019
- **Structure:** Nationwide alliance of 30+ member organizations including local chapters of national formations. Operates regional clusters with the goal of expanding to provincial and city level chapters.
- **National Coordinator:** Rachelle Junsay; **Spokespersons:** John Carl Cabangon, Mela Llamado
- **NCR Chapter:** Active in Metro Manila — held an art exhibit at Silingan Coffee in Quezon City
- **Website:** https://yacap.org/ ; Contact: https://yacap.org/contact/ ; Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/YACAPhilippines/ ; Manila Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/YACAP.PH/
- **Primary activities:** Climate justice advocacy, climate strikes, defense of environmental defenders, system change work, youth-led collective action. Strike pages and statement publications are dominant in public footprint.
- **Documentation today:** Heavy on press statements (statements on flood control infrastructure proposals, Loss & Damage Fund hosting, etc.) and Facebook activity. The 30+ member orgs each maintain their own social media; aggregation across the alliance appears manual.
- **DRR connection:** Indirect. YACAP framing is climate-justice-first; DRR appears in the UNICEF DRR National Consultation participation but is not the primary frame.
- **Institutional partners:** UNICEF Philippines (referenced in DRR consultation), 350 Pilipinas (allied), AEYN regional network. Identified in the Library of Congress web archive collection (https://www.loc.gov/item/lcwaN0004689/) — institutional documentation of the organization's significance.
- **Public-post evidence of documentation gap:** YACAP publishes statements but not member-org impact rollups. The alliance structure means a YACAP statement reflects the alliance, but the actual *projects* of the 30+ members are decentralized across their own Facebook pages — no central place to see "what did all YACAP members do in 2024."
- **Suggested interview question:** "Imagine you needed to show a partner like UNICEF or ICSC the total ground-level impact across all 30+ YACAP member organizations in the last year. How would you put that together today? Where does the data live?"

