## Section 4: Newly Discovered Organizations (Tier 3)

**Y4CJ Cagayan de Oro Chapter** *(11/15)*
- Anchored at Xavier University NSTP 2 in CDO. May 2024 climate-emergency petition with 3,000 signatures to the CDO Vice-Mayor's office. Partners with the Philippine Movement for Climate Justice (PMCJ) and a coalition of 6 CDO/Mindanao schools (Golden Heritage Polytechnic State College, Pilgrim Christian College, Southern Philippines College, USTSP, Capitol University, Xavier University, Archdiocese of Cagayan de Oro).
- Scores well on on-ground action and documentation gap but loses 2 accessibility points (Mindanao-based; in-person interview impractical within a week).
- **Best contact:** Through Xavier University NSTP program at https://www.xu.edu.ph/ or Philippine Movement for Climate Justice as a referral path.
- **Add to outreach list?** Yes, as a Week 2 / online-only target — strong fit for the user model, but not for in-person interview within current week.

**LCOY Philippines / Mindanao Local Conference of Youth** *(scored as event, not organization)*
- Recurring national youth climate conference (Oct 2025 conference held in Quezon City; Mindanao LCOY also active). Not a standalone organization but a high-yield event for finding the founder's other future targets. AYEJ reference: https://ayej.org/2025/11/25/lcoymindanao/
- **Strategic note:** Skim the LCOY Philippines participant lists/speaker rosters as a discovery channel for additional Tier-1-quality orgs to add later.

**Salcedo Youth Advocates / municipal-level structures** *(implicit through ICSC coverage)*
- ICSC documents Salcedo (E. Samar) as a youth-DRR exemplar. Sudao G.R.E.E.N. Minds is the visible org but the ICSC piece suggests broader municipal youth engagement. Worth asking Sudao directly about other Salcedo-based youth structures.

**YES-O (Youth for Environment in Schools Organization, DepEd)** *(14/15 rubric, structurally different)*
- Strictly by rubric, YES-O scores highest of any organization assessed — DepEd-mandated under DO 72 s. 2003, present in every public school nationwide, on-ground activity (cleanups, tree planting, ESWM) is built into the mandate. But: **YES-O chapters are gatekept by school administrators and teacher advisers, not by independent youth leaders.** This makes them inappropriate as Week 1 founder interview targets (you'd be interviewing a teacher, not a youth-org leader). They are the right scaling channel later via DepEd partnerships, not the right user interview now.

